    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PeruTM10.9">
<l>ceṟitavaccam pukaṉṟaṉaic ceṉṟu koṉṟu ceḻumaṟaiyō ṉuyirmīṭṭu tavattō ṉīnta</l>
<l>niṟaimaṇippū ṇaṇiyuṅkoṇ ṭilavaṇaṉ ṟaṉṉait tampiyāl vāṉēṟṟi muṉivaṉ vēṇṭat</l>
<l>tiṟalviḷaṅku milakkumaṉaip pirintāṉ ṟaṉṉait tillainakart tiruccitra kūṭan taṉṉuḷ</l>
<l>ḷuṟaivāṉai maṟavāta vuḷḷan taṉṉai yuṭaiyōmmaṟ ṟuṟutuyara maṭaiyō maṉṟē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>We who possess a heart that does not forget</l>
<l rend="indent">Him who lives inside Tiruccitrakūṭam in the town of Tillai,</l>
<l rend="indent">who, having gone [and] killed Śambuka of abundant tapas,</l>
<l rend="indent">recovered the life of the excellent brahmin,</l>
<l rend="indent">acquired wearable ornaments with splendid gems given by the sage,</l>
<l rend="indent">lifted up Lavaṇa to heaven by means of [His] younger brother</l>
<l rend="indent">[and] became parted from Lakṣmaṇa shining with valour as the sage had requested,</l>
<l>shall not suffer again from the grief that occurs, is it not [so]?</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
